    # game/areas/foggylake1structure.rpy:1955
    old "You chop and grind over two dozen of various herbs into a green pulp, making an ointment with a strong, woundworty smell, then mix it with the juice of carefully squeezed marshbules, clean of any seeds and peels. So far, so good. \n\nThen you spend long, long minutes at the table, constantly keeping the liquid on the brink of boiling, every now and then lowering and raising the small cauldron that hangs above the flame of an oil lamp. The boredom bites your fingers, but you don’t even have the time to go grab some water to drink. \n\nYou think of the alchemists who spend day after day repeating this procedure in their workshops. Hardly a tempting vision. \n\nAt least the room is now filled with a pleasant aroma, and according to what you hear from the conversations that take place upstairs, the smell reaches the main hall as well. You pour the grass-green liquid into one of the earthenware bottles, then seal it. The potion is ready. "
